# IAI-IPS Symbolic Cognition System README (Updated)

## Overview

The IAI-IPS Symbolic Cognition System enables quantum-neural hybrid computation using declarative symbolic dialectics. It is designed for bridging cognitive architectures in UBCI/SynapseLink systems.

## Key Features

* Declarative symbolic language for entanglement-based cognition.
* Quantum state management and coherence control.
* Neural activation and pattern integration.
* Logos â†” Pathos Twine cognition orchestration.
* Supports layered contradiction analysis.
* Ready for quantum hardware and BCI signal extensions.

## Repository Structure

* `core/`: Interpreter and symbolic engine modules.
* `docs/`: Architecture diagrams, LaTeX papers.
* `tests/`: Symbolic test pipelines.
* `data/`: Symbolic test datasets.

## Usage Example

```python
from iai_ips_symbolic_system import execute_statement

statements = [
    "DECLARE QuantumNeuralLink Q1",
    "ENTANGLE Q1 Q2",
    "MEASURE Q1",
    "ACTIVATE focus_pattern",
    "SWITCHMODE P"
]

for stmt in statements:
    execute_statement(stmt)
```

## Symbol Table

| Symbol          | Description             |
| --------------- | ----------------------- |
| PSI\_C / PSI\_D | Coherence / Decoherence |
| NABLA\_I        | Internal contradiction  |
| L\_ERROR        | Logos error signal      |
| M\_UNEASE       | Pathos unease signal    |
| D / G / H / P   | Learning modes          |

## Testing

Run:

```bash
python -m tests.run_all
```

